<div class="colorful3">
  {{> header wellness=true}}
  <div class="fullwide">
    <div class="mainheader midbound">
      <h1>Cats, dogs, and more.</h1>
      <h4>Wellness is an integration that connects to your Discord server and aids with mental health of users.</h4>
      <img class="headerimg" src="imgs/Wellness.png">
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<hr>
<div class="midbound">
  <div class="indexflexdiv">
    <div class="indexflexitem">
      <h5>If it's cute, it's here.</h5>
      <p>Wellness serves more than 12 different types of animals and 2 types of foods. Don't see what you like? You can request it to be added on the <a href="/ext/discord" class="standardlink">support discord</a>.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="indexflexitem">
      <h5>You matter too.</h5>
      <p>Wellness helps you get in touch with support groups, and do breathing exercises.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="indexflexitem">
      <h5>Involve your friends.</h5>
      <p>Remember all those image types mentioned before? If need be, you can send them to a friend - without alerting anyone else of anything.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="indexflexitem">
      <h5>Set boundaries.</h5>
      <p>Don't want people to spam you, or to receive messages from Wellness at all? That's okay! You can disable messaging functionality with a simple command.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="indexflexitem">
      <h5>Verified and secure.</h5>
      <p>Wellness is part of Discord's official bot verification program, and has that wonderful checkmark to show it. Your message contents are not read by the bot.</p>
    </div>
  </div>
</div>
<hr>
<div class="midbound">
  <h3>What are you waiting for?</h3>
  <p><a href="/ext/wellnessadd" class="button">Add Wellness</a></p>
</div>
{{> footer}}
